{
  "name": "Void Specialization",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/magic/symbols/elements-air-earth-fire-water.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When you choose this tradition at 2nd level, you learn two ninjutsu that you qualify for one of which can be C-Rank. </p><p>The chosen jutsu cannot have any nature release keywords. </p><p>You also gain a 1d6 bonus on all Ninshou checks related to ninjutsu without nature release keywords that you have the ability to cast. </p><p>Finally, when you cast a ninjutsu without any nature release, you can do one of the following, per casting:</p><p>• Once per casting, impose a -3 penalty to an affected creature's Concentration Check.</p><p>• Once per casting, impose a -3 penalty to an affected creature's Clash Check</p>",
